questions.text:
Calculate the energy released during fission of 1 kg of U235 as per following fission process:
$$ {^1_0}n + {^{235}_{92}}U \rightarrow {^{141}_{56}}Ba + {^{92}_{36}}Kr + 3{^1_0}n + \gamma $$
Assume masses of different elements and particles in unified atomic mass scale, u, (1u = $1.6604 \times 10^{-27}$ kg) are: $m_n$: 1.00879u; $m_U$: 234.9855u; $m_{Ba}$: 137.8716u; $m_{Kr}$: 94.877u;
